<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910606-0015</DOCNO><DOCID>910606-0015.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- McDonnell Douglas Corp.:   LOT Polish Airlines to Pay   $350 Million for MD-80 Jets</HL><DATE>06/06/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   BA F.ABI MD</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AIRLINES (AIR)AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><RE>EASTERN EUROPE (EEU)EUROPE (EU)FRANCE (FR)MISSOURI (MO)NORTH AMERICA (NME)POLAND (PL)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)WASHINGTON (WA)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   McDonnell Douglas Corp. said LOT Polish Airlines, thenational airline of Poland, signed a letter of intent topurchase nine MD-80 twin jets for about $350 million.   The first airplanes are scheduled for delivery to LOT inthe first quarter of 1992, with the remainder to be deliveredthrough 1993. LOT plans to use the short-to-medium-rangejetliners on European, North African and Middle Easternroutes.</LP><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas, which is based in St. Louis, said thismarks the first sale of its commercial airliners in Poland.&quot;It was a very tough competition,&quot; said company marketingchief Russell Ray, noting that the MD-80 won out overofferings from Boeing Co. and Airbus Industrie.</TEXT></DOC>